The paper deals with the trade-off between accuracy and test-time computational cost of deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses theoretical considerations and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments involve recognition data-sets and models, which are related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
